<TITLE> Stocks continue downward trend </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 18 (bdnews24.com)  Dhaka stocks continued to fall Tuesday, driven by the main DGEN or general index. Although the power sector was upbeat, the banking sector including market leader BRAC Bank slipped. The DGEN or general index declined 2.01 points or 0.08 percent to 2509.63. The DSI or all-share price index dipped 4.7 points or 0.23 percent to 2073.06. A total of 9,306,769 shares worth Tk 1.05 billion traded on the day. Of the traded issues, 80 gained, 96 declined and 25 remained unchanged. All the indices on the Chittagong Stock Exchange also ended lower with losers beating gainers 46 to 43. Nine scrips held steady. Turnover on the CSE finished lower at Tk 139.29 million from Monday's Tk 176.24 million. On the DSE, turnover leader BRAC Bank declined to Tk 1241 from Tk 1,264.25 Monday. AB Bank also fell to Tk 2230.75 from Tk 2270.75 but UCBL rose to Tk 4399.75 from Tk 4302.50. Power stocks regained, led by Power Grid Company of Bangladesh and DESCO. Power Grid added to close at Tk 622.75 from Tk 616 while DESCO traded at Tk 1142.75 from Tk 1141 the previous day. Among others in the top ten, South East Bank, Summit Power, Union Cap and AIMS 1st Mutual Fund traded upbeat while Square Pharma fell. bdnews
